msItem.note:
Two excerpts from the Vita beati Aegidii Ord. Praed.
. The original Vita, written by friar Pedro de Pais shortly after Gil's death in 1265, is no longer extant but was re-written c. 1567 by André de Resende, whose text was used for the Vita in the Acta sanctorum ( Schenk (2011)
). The text transmitted by the manuscript is close to verbatim of this edition.

Quotation ascribed to Seneca followed by a list of the characteristics of mortal sinners, a quotation ascribed here to Augustine, elsewhere to Bernard of Clairvaux (
                                        PL


                                    ), and an excerpt from the passion of St Eulalia of Mérida found in the Iberian tradition of passionaries (
                                        Passionarium Hispanicum saeculi decimi

                                    ).

note.p:
followed by excerpts from Livy, Petrarch, Ennodius, Lucan, Bernard of Clairvaux, and Seneca, as well as one quotation attributed to Josephus and found in the Liber scintillarum of Defensor Locociagensis (
                                            PL


                                        ), one ascribed to Seneca, and one to Gregory I.
